                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nc5sz52/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n                              <p>\n                                        <add>לאיש אשר אלה לו התורה והחכמה הדעת והתבונה ידידי וידיד\n                                                  נפשי</add>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>\n                                        <date>29th Tebet 5611</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Revd and dear Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I have <sic>considerd</sic> it a religious\n                                        duty<lb/> on my part to address this day a Pastoral letter\n                                        to the<lb/> much respect <persName>A. Hart Esq.</persName>\n                                        President of your Congregation<lb/> to endeavour a\n                                        reconciliation for indeed I must confess<lb/> fearless of\n                                        any one that you Sir as a <add>כי ביצחק יקרא החכם השלם יצחק\n                                                  בן אורי ז\"ן בן אליעזר</add><lb/> cannot in any way\n                                        be removed unless proper evidence<lb/> of any <add>יזנ\"ה אתו\n                                                  את הברכה מהברכה העליונה יהי שלום בחילו אין שטן\n                                                  ואין</add> be regularly taken by Orthodox and<lb/>\n                                        authenticated Jewish Ecclesiastics, thus I says if they<lb/>\n                                        really wish to be reputed as Jews which I doubt<lb/> not but\n                                        they are I have written to say that I am in<lb/> full hopes\n                                        that shortly every member at\n                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> will\n                                        loudly cry <add>פגע רע רק השקט ובטחה על אויביו יתגבר ולא\n                                                  תעשינה ידיהם תושיה</add> I regret that<lb/> the\n                                        days are very short (<date>Friday's</date>) and my\n                                        occupations<lb/> are numerous otherwise I should send you a\n                                        copy<lb/> I trust they will do all that is right. I have\n                                        read<lb/> the whole of your letter attentively—now my\n                                        Dr.<lb/> friend let me urge upon you and request it as\n                                        a<lb/> particular favor as a brother or a child pray\n                                        give<lb/> in (consistently) in whatever you can <add>מבקשי\n                                                  רעתו</add><lb/> pray <sic>dont</sic> be hasty till\n                                        all over <add>שליח צבור מוחזק מכמה שנים</add>\n                                        <sic>dont</sic> allow your<lb/> enemies to laugh, enter, be\n                                                  reinstated—<add>פסול חלילה</add> I doubt<lb/> not\n                                        you will do it and will fully understand my meaning and<lb/>\n                                        feelings—write to me <sic>dont</sic> spare me point out to\n                                        me I am ready<lb/> and willing to serve you as I see you are\n                                        in the right</p>\n                              "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nc5sz52/canvas/p2"
